        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 22 at 4:55PM CDT by NWS Shreveport LA</headline>
        <description>At 454 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 9
miles north of Flatwoods, or 9 miles northwest of Lena, moving
northeast at 55 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Cloutierville, Melrose, Lake Iatt, Montgomery, Chopin, Aloha, Colfax,
and Gorum.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
